<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-397-974  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 397 974.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  July 1989 v14 n7 p24L(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;Y CEO preaches standards, cooperation, and ATandamp;T Unix. (RobertE. Allen) (Special news supplement)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A T and T chief executive officer Robert E Allen discussed ISDN,Unix, industry standards, and global competitiveness in hiskeynote address at the 1989 Interface trade show in New York.andO;Allen called for cooperation among competing vendors ofinformation technology, noting that intense competition and lackof standards has created a mass of incompatible data.andP;  He statedthat standards 'liberate' creative use of technology by avoiding'artificial restrictions.' The Unix operating system was the focusof a quarter of Allen's speech.andP;  Allen reiterated that A T and Tdoes not seek to gain unfair advantage by controlling Unix andcited the formation of the Unix International consortium, which AT and T backs.andP;  He also added that A T and T installed over200,000 ISDN lines in 1988 and that the company is committed toproviding an all-digital network by 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (conferences and meetings).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     InterfaceTrade showsStandardizationUNIXCommunications TechnologyConnectivity.andO;Person:    Allen, Robert E. (addresses, essays, lectures).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>